race.comment: WIREWALKER (8) has won two of his past three starts and is racing with a lot of confidence of late. Drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. PRINCE LEVI (14) placed over this track and trip last time out and will be ready to show his best third-up from the break. Only needs some luck navigating from the sticky draw to be playing a major role in the outcome. PERFECT PLAY (3) has placed two from two over this distance range and doesn't know how to put in a poor one. Don't discount lightly. The well-related LARRIKIN ROGUE (6) (half to G3 winner Shamalia) didn't measure up in Listed grade at the latest outing but will find this task a touch easier. Watch for sharp improvement. ZAPHOD (2) next in line out of the Lees camp.
